Police have arraigned a 27-year-old man, Olubunmi Boluwaji, before a Magistrates’ Court sitting in Ado Ekiti for allegedly defiling a minor. Boluwaji, who was standing trial on one count charge of rape committed the offence on March 9, this year in Ikere-Ekiti The police prosecutor, Sgt.Olubu Apata, told the court that the defendant allegedly defiled a 9-year-old girl, and used handkerchief to clean her blood. The offence according to the prosecutor contravened Section 31 of the Child Right Law of Ekiti State 2012. Apata asked the court for adjournment to enable him duplicate the case file and send it to the office of Director of Public Prosecution (DPP) for issuance of legal advice while defendant’s plea was not taken. The Magistrate, Mrs Kehinde Awosika, ordered that the defendant be kept in police custody pending issuance of legal advice from DPP. She subsequently adjourned the case till March 24 for mention.